<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="337" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[835,1474,1309,1621]" pageId="8" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,967,1309,1333]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="337">Discussion.</emphasis>
— The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1914" box="[1144,1229,1310,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Saldidae" genus="Saldula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1144,1229,1310,1333]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="337">Saldula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most speciose genus in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[981,1076,1341,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Saldidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Saldidae</taxonomicName>
, and is distributed worldwide, from the tropics to the arctic, occurring on every continent except 
<collectingCountry box="[835,954,1405,1429]" name="Antarctica" pageId="8" pageNumber="337">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
. Diagnostic characters for this genus include the presence of an oblique secondary hypocostal ridge that intersects with the costal margin midway between the embolar base and the fracture (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1169,1298,1501,1525]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[835,881,2033,2055]" captionTargetBox="[836,1468,957,1978]" captionTargetId="figure-8@6.[814,1487,945,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 12–14. Hypocostal ridge structures of saldid genera: 12, Saldula; 13, Pentacora; 14, Rupisalda (all after J. Polhemus, 1985)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5348123" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5348123/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="337">Figs. 12–14</figureCitation>
), reduced ocelli, and the callus of the pronotum bearing a well-defined pit (J. 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus, J" box="[872,1054,1565,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="337" refId="ref10089" refString="Polhemus, J. T., 1985. Shorebugs (Heteroptera: Hemiptera; Saldidae): A World Overview and Taxonomy of Middle American Forms. The Different Drummer, Englewood, Colorado. v + 252 pp." type="book" year="1985">Polhemus, 1985</bibRefCitation>
). Two species are known to occur in Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[956,1057,1597,1621]" name="Malaysia" pageId="8" pageNumber="337">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
